## Installing spark.phar

The easy way to install spark is using `spark.phar`. A `.phar` file is a compiled php script that includes all of the things it needs to run in a single file.

{% endmarkdown %}

<a class="button" href="/binaries/v0.3.0/spark.phar">Download spark.phar</a>

{% markdown %}

To make it easier to run spark commands, we'll next want to move spark to be on our `path`. This means that our terminal will know how to find spark without us having to tell it the full path to the .phar file. On OSX and Linux, you can do this via:

    $ sudo mv spark.phar /usr/local/bin/spark
    $ sudo chmod +x /usr/local/bin/spark

`sudo` may not be necessary on your computer, but it shouldn't break anything either.

You can verify that spark is installed by running `spark` from your terminal. You should see the command output:

