## Installing from Source

In order to install Spark from source, you'll need to have the following prerequisites installed:

- [git](http://git-scm.com/downloads)
- php 5.3 or higher
- [Composer](http://getcomposer.org/)

Once the prerequisites are satisfied, clone spark and install the dependencies:

    $ git clone git@gh.riotgames.com:cbednarski/spark.git
    $ cd spark
    $ composer install

Finally, install spark in `/usr/local/bin`:

    $ sudo ln -s $PWD/bin/spark /usr/local/bin/spark

Spark should now be in your path, which means you can type `spark` at the terminal and see a list of commands.

## Building the .phar File

`spark.phar` is built using [pharcc](https://github.com/cbednarski/pharcc), which you'll need to install before you continue. Once `pharcc` is installed you can compile `spark.phar` by running `pharcc build` in the project root, on any version after `v0.3.0`. Example:

    $ pharcc build
    Building spark.phar
    Build complete.

